OL,3,CCouple jailed for #270,000 benefits
OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FA woman who orchestrated a decade-long
OL,7,Fbenefits fraud involving fake names,
OL,8,Ffabricated medical conditions, and a
OL,9,Fnon-existent caravan has been jailed.
OL,11,FAngela Lloyd pretended to be a full-
OL,12,Ftime carer for her partner, and
OL,13,Ffabricated illnesses affecting her
OL,14,Fteenage son, as part of her scheme
OL,15,Fallowing her to unlawfully claim
OL,16,Fnearly #170,000 in benefits since 2012.
OL,18,FThe 58-year-old part-time care worker
OL,19,Falso took on multiple aliases,
OL,20,Fincluding that of a deceased woman, to
OL,21,Fdeceive authorities.
