OL,3,CCouple jailed for #270,000 benefits
OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FHer partner, Lee Phillips, 54, also
OL,7,Fbenefited from the fraud, claiming
OL,8,Fmore than #100,000 in welfare payments
OL,9,Fbetween 2018 and 2023.
OL,11,FLiverpool Crown Court heard how Lloyd
OL,12,Fclaimed a total of #169,394, which she
OL,13,Fwas not entitled to, in housing
OL,14,Fbenefit, personal independence
OL,15,Fpayments and carers allowance over the
OL,16,Fspan of 11-and-a-half years.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
