OL,3,CCouple jailed for #270,000 benefits
OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FHe also exaggerated his own medical
OL,7,Fconditions - claiming he was
OL,8,Fcompletely dependent on others - to
OL,9,Fgain more than #32,000 in pip and more
OL,10,Fthan #51,000 in employment support
OL,11,Fallowance.
OL,13,FHe later claimed Lloyd had filled out
OL,14,Fthe paperwork on his behalf.
OL,16,FPhillips' lawyer described him as a
OL,17,Fman with significant health issues,
OL,18,Fincluding diabetes, kidney failure,
OL,19,Fand heart problems.
