OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FHe now uses a wheelchair and receives
OL,7,Fdaily care. His defence argued that he
OL,8,Fwould be especially vulnerable in
OL,9,Fprison and highlighted that his
OL,10,Foriginal claims were legitimate before
OL,11,Fhe became involved with Lloyd.
OL,13,FLloyd's previous criminal record
OL,14,Fincludes various dishonesty offences
OL,15,Fdating back to the 1980s, although her
OL,16,Flast conviction was in 2012.
