OL,3,CCouple jailed for #270,000 benefits
OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FHer defence acknowledged her past but
OL,7,Femphasised that she had accepted
OL,8,Fresponsibility, remained employed, and
OL,9,Fwas making repayments. She also has
OL,10,Fongoing caring responsibilities for
OL,11,Fher son.
OL,13,FLloyd pleaded guilty to seven counts
OL,14,Fof fraud by false representation. She
OL,15,Fcried out in court as she was
OL,16,Fsentenced to two years in prison.
OL,18,FPhillips pleaded guilty to four fraud-
OL,19,Frelated charges and was sentenced to
OL,20,F20 months in prison.
