OL,3,CCouple jailed for #270,000 benefits
OL,4,Cfraud scheme
OL,6,FJudge Simon Medland KC said the pair
OL,7,Fhad committed a "substantial and
OL,8,Fdetermined fraud on the public purse,"
OL,9,Fdriven by "personal greed."
OL,11,FHe noted the use of fake addresses,
OL,12,Fstolen identities, and exaggerated
OL,13,Fmedical claims, particularly regarding
OL,14,Ftheir teenage son.
OL,16,F"To defraud the public of benefits
OL,17,Fmeant for those in genuine need is a
OL,18,Fserious offence," the judge said.
OL,20,F"The system relies on honesty. Those
OL,21,Fwho abuse it must face punishment."
